dct_title_s: A plan of Cuzco: ancient and modern
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures. Ancient buildings shown in black. Ancient roads and squares shown in brown. Includes index: Reference to the houses of Spanish conquerors A.D. 1555. Southern portion of Sacsayhuamán is shown. From: The Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 41 (1871), pp. 281-338; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1871.
